		"AbilityTooltips"
		{
			"special_bonus_attack_speed_30"		"Obviously, AS talent is better because silencer wants to transition into core and the only thing he needs to start dealing more damage is actually attack speed."
			"silencer_curse_of_the_silent"		"Main thing we need in ganks is slow. More powerful slow = more chances to kill. Because of that Arcane Curse becomes our main skill to max out. Another thing about it: it's actually ridiculous how much damage you can deal with it in fights, so you shouldn't underestimate it."
			"silencer_glaives_of_wisdom"		"While it's our damage dealing tool, we won't need it any time soon: Q or E after upgrade will deal much more damage, while also will allow us to actually kill people. Casting W manually on enemy while laning will allow us to harass opponents without creep aggro, so it's worth using skill point early"
			"silencer_last_word"		"Nuke, silence and vision on target in ganks.Pretty good to get it maxed out after curse (or sometimes even instead of it)"
			"special_bonus_intelligence_7"		"Both talents are good, but int will increase our damage output in fight and our farming speed, so it's usually better."
			"special_bonus_attack_range_200"		"Attack range is usually better choice since we want to be another core at this point and attack from decent range. Altho, Curse Slow talent is pretty good too and works well in fights (or with aghs)"
